WEBVTT

00:02.036 --> 00:03.382
[phone line ringing]
- Hey.

00:03.486 --> 00:04.797
I need your help with a case.

00:04.901 --> 00:06.972
- Aren't you supposed to be
on maternity leave?

00:07.041 --> 00:08.387
- What are you, my husband?

00:08.525 --> 00:10.286
- Look, forget I said anything.
What's up?

00:10.389 --> 00:11.977
- I have an open file
that's almost ready

00:12.046 --> 00:13.392
to hand off
to the DA's office.

00:13.530 --> 00:14.807
If I take care of it now,

00:14.911 --> 00:16.775
it won't be hanging
over my head when I get back.

00:16.878 --> 00:18.777
Wanna help me out?
- Sure.

00:18.880 --> 00:20.227
[door clicks]

00:20.365 --> 00:21.469
[quirky music]

00:21.538 --> 00:23.575
- What you doing?

00:23.678 --> 00:26.371
- Trying to figure out
the crib assembly.

00:26.509 --> 00:28.235
- In the closet?

00:28.373 --> 00:29.615
- It's peaceful in here.

00:29.719 --> 00:30.651
- Who's on the phone?

00:30.720 --> 00:32.238
- Customer service.

00:32.342 --> 00:34.655
- Do you have your
order number handy, ma'am?

00:35.966 --> 00:37.416
- Hi, Aaron.
- Hi.

00:37.520 --> 00:39.625
- Angela,
I know you're working.

00:39.729 --> 00:41.110
Wrap it up,

00:41.213 --> 00:42.663
or I'm gonna call Grey
and tell him what you're doing.

00:42.732 --> 00:43.905
- [sighs]

00:44.044 --> 00:46.529
In the future,
you could disguise your voice.

00:46.598 --> 00:48.910
- I'm not comfortable being
pulled into your web of lies.

00:49.014 --> 00:50.257
- Get over it.

00:50.395 --> 00:52.190
I need you to collect DNA
from a suspect.

00:52.259 --> 00:53.191
I'll text you his name.

00:53.260 --> 00:54.330
- Okay. Do we have a warrant?

00:54.399 --> 00:56.194
- No.

00:56.263 --> 00:58.541
- Then how am I supposed
to get his DNA?

00:58.610 --> 01:00.922
- You wanna be a detective?

01:01.026 --> 01:02.441
Figure it out.

01:02.545 --> 01:03.787
- ♪ I'm gonna win for you

01:03.891 --> 01:07.170
♪ Like I know
you want me to do ♪

01:07.274 --> 01:09.621
- All right, let's get to it.

01:09.759 --> 01:11.657
Special of the day:
Frank Teska.

01:11.761 --> 01:13.038
Frank spent two decades

01:13.107 --> 01:15.558
working his way up
from a street-level enforcer

01:15.627 --> 01:17.801
to a proud boss
of a renaissance crew

01:17.939 --> 01:20.804
that ran everything
from prostitutes to drugs.

01:20.908 --> 01:22.461
- Then Frank's temper
got the best of him.

01:22.599 --> 01:24.981
took an eight-year fall
for involuntary manslaughter.

01:25.085 --> 01:28.191
- Although there was nothing
involuntary about it.

01:28.295 --> 01:29.882
More recently--
that is, last week--

01:29.951 --> 01:31.574
Frank exited prison
and, we believe,

01:31.643 --> 01:32.713
took out his brother, Ed,

01:32.782 --> 01:34.646
to reestablish leadership.

01:34.783 --> 01:36.613
- We have prison intel
over Frank's

01:36.751 --> 01:38.132
last few months inside.

01:38.270 --> 01:39.547
He was making a push

01:39.651 --> 01:41.652
to get into
the ghost gun business.

01:41.791 --> 01:43.655
- Specifically,
3D-printed weapons,

01:43.758 --> 01:45.864
which are invisible
to metal detectors.

01:45.967 --> 01:46.865
Next-generation ghost guns

01:46.968 --> 01:48.866
are printed using
a high-strength,

01:48.970 --> 01:49.971
nylon-based polymer,

01:50.075 --> 01:51.973
which is illegal to buy in bulk

01:52.112 --> 01:53.491
without proper paperwork.

01:53.596 --> 01:55.943
- Now, this morning, METRO
raided Ridgeside Chemicals

01:56.012 --> 01:58.152
based on intel that Frank
was about to take a delivery

01:58.256 --> 01:59.843
of 300 gallons of that polymer.

01:59.981 --> 02:02.156
- Which leaves Frank
without a supplier.

02:02.294 --> 02:03.330
- Exactly.

02:03.433 --> 02:04.848
- Which is where
Officer Chen comes in.

02:04.986 --> 02:07.851
She'll be going undercover at
Southland Chemicals in Venice,

02:07.989 --> 02:09.853
the only other local
manufacturer of the polymer.

02:09.990 --> 02:11.821
- And I'll be living
at the Langholm apartments.

02:11.924 --> 02:13.685
- So until further notice,

02:13.823 --> 02:15.894
if you see Officer Chen
out in the world,

02:15.997 --> 02:17.240
do not acknowledge her.

02:17.344 --> 02:19.103
All those assigned to support,

02:19.173 --> 02:20.416
see Sergeant Bradford.

02:20.519 --> 02:22.487
Everyone else,
let's get to work.

02:22.625 --> 02:24.316
♪

02:26.525 --> 02:28.078
- Mornin'.
- Hey.

02:28.182 --> 02:29.528
- You feelin' all right?

02:29.666 --> 02:31.703
- Yeah, I'm just taking it
a little slow this morning.

02:31.806 --> 02:34.533
I, uh, saw some friends that
I haven't seen in a long time.

02:34.637 --> 02:36.535
- Oh, you need
a little carefree time.

02:36.639 --> 02:38.192
Just be careful
not to burn yourself out.

02:38.329 --> 02:40.712
- I won't, but ever since
we got justice for Blanca,

02:40.815 --> 02:42.886
it's like this weight
has been lifted,

02:43.024 --> 02:44.716
like my soul feels lighter,
you know what I mean?

02:44.853 --> 02:46.890
- I do, and I'm happy for you.

02:46.994 --> 02:49.721
- I even signed up
for this dating app, YouSpark.

02:49.824 --> 02:51.964
I can't remember the last time
I even flirted with a guy.

02:52.033 --> 02:53.621
- Well, let's hope
sparks fly soon.

02:53.725 --> 02:55.278
- Gotta love
a Daddy Cop joke.

02:55.382 --> 02:57.522
- Hey, I need you to run
down to the morgue for me.

02:57.625 --> 02:58.557
- Fun. Why?

02:58.661 --> 02:59.696
- Remember NoHo Doe?

02:59.834 --> 03:00.904
- I do.

03:01.008 --> 03:02.389
A torso found
in North Hollywood,

03:02.527 --> 03:03.562
no definitive cause of death,

03:03.700 --> 03:04.874
and no means to ID him.

03:04.977 --> 03:06.151
- It was a dead-end case
I took on

03:06.220 --> 03:08.049
to keep Skip Tracer Randy
out of jail.

03:08.153 --> 03:09.741
- Was that the right decision?

03:09.879 --> 03:12.675
- Definitely not,
but I have to solve it now.

03:12.744 --> 03:14.746
To that end, an arm was found

03:14.884 --> 03:16.644
near Silver Lake Reservoir
this morning.

03:16.748 --> 03:18.784
- Gotta be connected
to the torso, right?

03:18.888 --> 03:20.165
No--no pun intended.

03:20.234 --> 03:21.408
- Not necessarily.

03:21.511 --> 03:22.823
There are a surprising amount

03:22.892 --> 03:24.480
of severed limbs in this city.

03:24.549 --> 03:25.481
- Mm.

03:25.550 --> 03:28.173
♪

03:28.242 --> 03:29.623
- Oh.
- Kay.

03:29.726 --> 03:36.595
♪

03:36.733 --> 03:38.528
- Thorsen, what are you doing?

03:38.597 --> 03:39.702
- Looking for DNA.

03:39.771 --> 03:41.013
- It looks like
you're moonlighting

03:41.082 --> 03:42.601
at the sanitation department.

03:42.739 --> 03:44.154
- Yeah, I could see
how you could think that.

03:44.258 --> 03:46.916
You know,
it's not often that you find

03:47.019 --> 03:48.504
a young, budding detective

03:48.607 --> 03:51.369
with this amount of dedication
to solve a case.

03:51.438 --> 03:53.680
- Tell me you came by
this evidence legally.

03:53.785 --> 03:56.132
- I mean, I might've committed
a minor trespass

03:56.236 --> 03:59.618
to gather evidence,
but per police procedure.

03:59.722 --> 04:02.207
- Translation: you walked
on the suspect's property,

04:02.276 --> 04:03.519
dug through their trash bins,

04:03.622 --> 04:05.003
and brought
all their trash here.

04:05.106 --> 04:06.004
- Basically.

04:06.107 --> 04:07.039
- Well, you're not sorting

04:07.108 --> 04:09.007
through that filth
in my station.

04:09.110 --> 04:10.526
Get it out of here.

04:10.629 --> 04:11.527
And Thorsen,

04:11.630 --> 04:12.942
this table better be spotless

04:13.045 --> 04:14.599
when you're gone.

04:14.737 --> 04:16.290
- Yes, sir.

04:16.394 --> 04:17.360
- I called Hard Luck.

04:17.464 --> 04:18.361
- What--really?

04:18.464 --> 04:20.293
He's such an unreliable CI.

04:20.432 --> 04:22.158
- No, he's just a little
twitchy sometimes.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.471
He's the only informant I got
who has an in with Frank Teska.

04:24.609 --> 04:26.231
So he's gonna point Frank
in the direction

04:26.300 --> 04:27.715
of your new identity
at Southland.

04:27.819 --> 04:29.855
- Yeah, or he'll go
on a three-day bender

04:29.959 --> 04:31.305
and wake up in Reno.

04:31.409 --> 04:32.306
- No, he won't,

04:32.444 --> 04:33.721
'cause I told him
it was for you.

04:33.825 --> 04:35.378
He knows it's important to me.

04:35.482 --> 04:36.414
- Aw.

04:36.483 --> 04:38.312
Undercover love.

04:38.450 --> 04:40.452
[laughs]

04:40.521 --> 04:43.490
- I'm sorry to say the new arm
is not a match for NoHo Doe.

04:43.628 --> 04:45.284
- Yeah, I figured
it was too much to hope for.

04:45.354 --> 04:48.633
- But the method of amputation
on it is confounding.

04:48.771 --> 04:49.979
- How so?

04:50.117 --> 04:51.670
- I've never seen
such well-defined

04:51.774 --> 04:53.154
traumatic separation of tissue.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.156
I honestly don't know
what instrument was used

04:55.295 --> 04:56.503
to remove it.

04:56.641 --> 04:58.228
- A katana? Lightsaber.

04:58.332 --> 05:00.507
- No and no.

05:00.610 --> 05:03.510
- Any idea what was used
to chop up NoHo Doe?

05:03.613 --> 05:05.512
- Definitely a blade
done post-mortem,

05:05.650 --> 05:07.790
but I have no idea
what the cause of death was.

05:07.859 --> 05:10.344
I did find evidence
that your torso owner

05:10.448 --> 05:11.863
had a hip arthroplasty.

05:12.001 --> 05:14.831
- So if we find a severed limb
with hip hardware,

05:14.969 --> 05:16.281
it's most likely our guy?

05:16.350 --> 05:18.352
- Exactly,
and then I'll be able to ID him

05:18.490 --> 05:20.078
off the serial number.
- Outstanding.

05:20.181 --> 05:22.183
Thank you very much.
Shall we?

05:22.322 --> 05:24.185
Looks like we're going
on a leg hunt.

05:24.289 --> 05:25.670
- This job is so weird.

05:25.773 --> 05:26.843
- [chuckles]

05:31.054 --> 05:33.954
[Abby Holliday's
"Ohio Laundry Room"]

05:34.023 --> 05:37.267
♪

05:37.371 --> 05:38.683
- Hello.

05:38.786 --> 05:39.891
I'm Larry Ellis,

05:39.994 --> 05:42.859
and you must be Jamie Hall.

05:43.895 --> 05:46.553
I can't tell you how excited
I am to be part of this--

05:46.656 --> 05:47.623
- Oh, uh--uh,

05:47.726 --> 05:49.210
it's nice to meet you too,
Larry.

05:49.349 --> 05:51.627
Um, maybe you could show me
to my office.

05:51.730 --> 05:53.283
- ♪ Just in time for summer

05:53.387 --> 05:55.147
- It's not the right leg.
- It is a right leg.

05:55.216 --> 05:57.736
- No, I mean
it's not the correct leg.

05:57.840 --> 05:59.289
- But we'll take it
off your hands.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.499
- [sighs] 20 bucks.

06:01.568 --> 06:03.501
Five?

06:03.570 --> 06:05.468
- Anything you need, I'm here.

06:05.572 --> 06:07.505
So just let me know.
[chuckles]

06:07.574 --> 06:11.301
And again,
I am so happy to help the LAPD.

06:11.405 --> 06:13.407
"NYPD Blue"
is my favorite TV show,

06:13.511 --> 06:14.650
so you can imagine.

06:14.753 --> 06:17.204
- Uh, Larry,
I really appreciate the offer,

06:17.273 --> 06:19.240
but you know, the best thing
you could do for me

06:19.379 --> 06:21.415
is to treat me like
all your other employees.

06:21.519 --> 06:23.037
And you know, this should
really be the last time

06:23.106 --> 06:25.488
that you mention the LAPD,
okay?

06:25.592 --> 06:27.007
- Yes, of course.

06:27.076 --> 06:28.146
Copy that.

06:28.249 --> 06:30.044
[chuckles]

06:30.113 --> 06:32.530
Uh, I've been practicing
all the lingo.

06:32.599 --> 06:33.531
- No lingo.

06:33.600 --> 06:35.705
- No lingo.
- Yeah, okay.

06:35.774 --> 06:38.536
I'm just a regular
plastics salesperson.

06:38.605 --> 06:39.985
- [clicks tongue]
[chuckles]

06:40.089 --> 06:41.504
- ♪ I will never blame you

06:41.608 --> 06:43.989
♪ You were dealt
a hell of a hand ♪

06:44.093 --> 06:46.440
♪ If I were you

06:46.544 --> 06:49.270
♪ I would have done

06:49.374 --> 06:52.273
♪ The same thing

06:52.412 --> 06:53.516
[phone ringing]

06:53.620 --> 06:55.691
♪ If I were you

06:55.794 --> 06:56.864
- Jamie Hall.

06:56.968 --> 06:58.348
- You all set up, Jamie?

06:58.452 --> 07:00.074
- Yeah, all good.

07:00.143 --> 07:02.629
Although we should probably
keep an eye on my boss.

07:02.732 --> 07:05.459
He's a little overeager.

07:05.563 --> 07:06.805
- Want me to have
a talk with him?

07:06.909 --> 07:08.876
- No, no. I've got it.

07:08.980 --> 07:11.085
Are you good?
- Yeah.

07:11.154 --> 07:12.362
Yeah, we got you covered
out here.

07:12.466 --> 07:13.571
Wherever you go, we go.

07:13.640 --> 07:14.882
- Well, that's comforting,

07:14.986 --> 07:17.782
but I meant, like,
are yougood?

07:18.990 --> 07:21.199
- Do you mean
do I miss you already?

07:21.302 --> 07:22.200
No.

07:22.303 --> 07:23.960
I'm fine.

07:24.064 --> 07:26.480
- You are such a jerk.

07:26.618 --> 07:29.000
Hey, will you keep an eye
on Tamara for me?

07:29.138 --> 07:31.312
You know, just check in on her
every once in a while?

07:31.416 --> 07:32.831
- Of course.
And don't worry about her.

07:32.969 --> 07:33.832
I'll keep an eye on her.

07:33.970 --> 07:36.317
You just focus on the job.

07:36.456 --> 07:37.767
- ♪ Even if it takes

07:37.836 --> 07:39.838
- How long do you think
this'll take?

07:39.976 --> 07:41.668
- Day, week, couple months.

07:41.771 --> 07:43.048
Hard to tell.

07:43.152 --> 07:46.017
- Oh, do not finish

07:46.120 --> 07:48.053
this season of "Top Chef"
without me.

07:48.157 --> 07:50.504
- I can't make any promises.

07:50.642 --> 07:53.403
- You ever wish
you had a normal job?

07:53.507 --> 07:55.889
- One where people
don't shoot at you?

07:55.992 --> 07:57.511
Not once.

07:57.649 --> 08:00.238
- [chuckles]
Yeah, me either.

08:00.341 --> 08:02.447
- ♪ Ooh, ooh

08:02.516 --> 08:05.519
♪ Ooh

08:05.623 --> 08:06.624
- False alarm.

08:06.693 --> 08:08.246
It's only a foot.

08:08.349 --> 08:12.526
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

08:12.630 --> 08:14.148
- Making any friends?

08:14.217 --> 08:16.634
- There's a lovely lady,
Delores.

08:16.703 --> 08:18.082
She's got a lot
of cute stories

08:18.187 --> 08:19.878
about her grandkids.

08:20.016 --> 08:21.707
This past weekend, apparently,

08:21.811 --> 08:24.434
little Jimbo ate
a dozen marbles.

08:24.538 --> 08:26.195
- Well, well, well.

08:26.332 --> 08:28.404
what do we have here?

08:28.508 --> 08:31.959
- I've been going through
this dude's trash for days,

08:32.063 --> 08:35.169
and I can't find a single thing
with his DNA on it.

08:35.238 --> 08:36.549
Seems pretty impossible, right?

08:36.688 --> 08:38.725
'Cause I basically leave
a trail of DNA everywhere I go.

08:38.863 --> 08:40.727
- Whoa, whoa, TMX.

08:40.830 --> 08:44.039
- It's actually "TMI," Smitty.
"Too much information."

08:44.144 --> 08:46.111
- Pretty sure I'm right.

08:48.735 --> 08:49.874
- Earwax.

08:49.977 --> 08:51.634
Yes. Let's go.

08:56.259 --> 08:58.330
- Is the monotony
getting to you?

08:58.399 --> 08:59.918
- I don't mind it.

09:00.056 --> 09:02.507
I just don't want it all
to be for nothing.

09:02.576 --> 09:04.129
Frank must be in a rush
to make those guns

09:04.233 --> 09:05.234
and get paid.

09:05.372 --> 09:07.270
Can't be much longer.

09:07.408 --> 09:08.858
- I'm sure
he's checking you out,

09:08.927 --> 09:11.551
seeing if the story
Hard Luck has fed him is true.

09:16.763 --> 09:17.695
[car door opens]

09:17.764 --> 09:18.696
[tense music]

09:18.765 --> 09:19.697
- Hi.

09:19.766 --> 09:20.698
- Good morning.

09:20.767 --> 09:21.837
- We need to talk.

09:21.906 --> 09:22.872
♪

09:22.941 --> 09:24.840
- Uh, I'm sorry.

09:24.943 --> 09:25.875
Do I know you?

09:25.944 --> 09:27.774
- No, but I know you.

09:27.877 --> 09:29.845
I know your real name's
not Jamie Hall.

09:33.089 --> 09:34.194
- Look, I don't know
what you're talking about,

09:34.297 --> 09:35.333
but if you'd like
to buy plastics,

09:35.436 --> 09:36.714
I'm happy to invite you in.

09:36.783 --> 09:39.855
Otherwise...
- Lisa Thompson.

09:39.958 --> 09:41.719
Born in Flagstaff,

09:41.788 --> 09:44.342
currently wanted
on two counts of felon fraud

09:44.445 --> 09:46.378
for cashing bad checks.

09:46.482 --> 09:48.622
Now, you want me to go inside
and tell your boss,

09:48.726 --> 09:50.624
or are you gonna take
a little ride with me?

09:50.728 --> 09:53.696
[tense music]

09:53.800 --> 09:55.802
♪

09:55.940 --> 09:57.182
- Why don't we go for a walk?

09:57.286 --> 10:04.189
♪

10:07.986 --> 10:11.058
So what do you want?

10:11.162 --> 10:13.060
- To get to know each other
a little better.

10:13.164 --> 10:17.962
If we're gonna be in business,
we gotta establish a rapport.

10:18.100 --> 10:19.308
Trust.

10:19.446 --> 10:21.551
- Who said
we're doing business?

10:21.655 --> 10:22.794
- Me.

10:24.485 --> 10:28.006
- Look, I came to LA
to start over,

10:28.144 --> 10:33.011
so I am very respectfully
just gonna pass, okay?

10:33.115 --> 10:36.014
- Yeah, well,
that's not really an option.

10:36.152 --> 10:39.017
I need access
to certain protected plastics,

10:39.155 --> 10:41.433
and you need
to not go to prison.

10:41.537 --> 10:44.022
But this is a very
low-risk thing for you.

10:44.160 --> 10:46.680
A few barrels a month
get misplaced.

10:46.818 --> 10:49.027
That kind of loss is normal,

10:49.165 --> 10:52.203
and it's built into
the company's profit margin.

10:52.341 --> 10:54.999
I just need you
to hide the missing inventory

10:55.102 --> 10:56.656
from your boss.

10:56.725 --> 11:01.005
You do that, and I'll pay you
5,000 bucks a month, huh?

11:01.143 --> 11:02.282
How's that sound?

11:03.766 --> 11:06.389
- Tempting, but I think
I would just prefer

11:06.527 --> 11:08.219
to give my notice today
and let you make this deal

11:08.322 --> 11:10.462
with the next girl
that sits behind my desk.

11:10.566 --> 11:13.431
- Look, I'm trying
to be nice here, hmm?

11:13.534 --> 11:16.227
But the alternative
to you saying yes

11:16.330 --> 11:18.781
is me drowning you
in that canal.

11:18.885 --> 11:22.854
So how about you get onboard,
like, right now?

11:22.958 --> 11:24.373
♪

11:24.476 --> 11:25.719
- Yeah,
when you put it that way,

11:25.857 --> 11:27.065
I guess I'm in.

11:27.203 --> 11:29.205
- Great.
We'll have dinner tonight?

11:29.343 --> 11:30.897
Hammer out the details, hmm?

11:31.000 --> 11:33.278
I'll pick you up at your place
at 8:00?

11:33.382 --> 11:34.383
- Okay.

11:34.486 --> 11:35.556
- Good.

11:35.660 --> 11:42.563
♪

11:44.117 --> 11:45.981
- [laughs] Liar.

11:46.050 --> 11:47.741
Liar.

11:47.879 --> 11:49.398
Mentiroso.

11:49.536 --> 11:50.744
Liar.

11:50.848 --> 11:52.919
- So how goes
the online dating?

11:53.057 --> 11:55.749
- Uh, a giant cesspool
of self-absorbed narcissists

11:55.887 --> 11:57.578
with no love to give.
- [chuckles]

11:57.717 --> 11:58.925
Sounds like my childhood.

11:59.028 --> 12:00.581
And yet, you're still swiping.

12:00.720 --> 12:01.582
- I mean, just look.

12:01.721 --> 12:02.825
They all look so good,
you know?

12:02.929 --> 12:04.033
And then you do
a little digging

12:04.102 --> 12:06.035
and find out they're actually
ten years older,

12:06.104 --> 12:08.348
four inches shorter,
married with children,

12:08.451 --> 12:10.350
and just looking
for a side piece.

12:10.419 --> 12:12.421
Prime example.

12:12.559 --> 12:14.147
- Oh, he's handsome

12:14.250 --> 12:15.873
and not unfamiliar.

12:15.942 --> 12:17.081
That's...

12:18.013 --> 12:20.015
Oh, my God! Is that Smitty?
- I know.

12:20.118 --> 12:21.775
I mean, he was a slice.

12:21.879 --> 12:24.191
But that is false advertisement
for a profile pic.

12:24.260 --> 12:25.883
- I'll say.

12:25.952 --> 12:27.436
- How did you and Bailey meet?

12:27.574 --> 12:28.851
- Oh.

12:30.197 --> 12:32.268
She just showed up
at my door one day.

12:32.406 --> 12:35.133
A gorgeous, multitalented,

12:35.271 --> 12:37.860
half-naked woman
wrapped in a towel.

12:37.964 --> 12:39.448
And now we're engaged.

12:39.586 --> 12:41.795
- I hate you.
- [chuckles]

12:41.899 --> 12:45.040
My point is I wasn't looking.

12:45.143 --> 12:46.524
That's when love shows up.

12:48.319 --> 12:50.079
- 7-Adam-15,
RP found a leg

12:50.148 --> 12:51.322
at the Hollywood Reservoir.

12:51.460 --> 12:53.773
Do you want the call?
- Yep.

12:56.154 --> 12:58.467
- Hey.
You called about the leg?

12:58.570 --> 12:59.986
- Yes. Uh, Scott.

13:00.089 --> 13:02.505
We were out for a walk,
and Buddy here found it.

13:02.643 --> 13:04.335
I've been trying
to get him to let go,

13:04.473 --> 13:06.475
but he's become quite attached.

13:06.578 --> 13:07.821
- Oh, no problem.

13:07.925 --> 13:09.098
All we have to do
is offer him something

13:09.167 --> 13:11.514
he wants more
than a severed leg.

13:11.618 --> 13:12.826
- Do you always carry
dog treats?

13:12.930 --> 13:14.000
- Yeah. Tip from a friend.

13:14.138 --> 13:15.415
Hey, Buddy. Here you go.

13:15.484 --> 13:16.554
Here you...
[dog growling]

13:16.657 --> 13:18.004
Easy, easy.
[dog barks]

13:18.142 --> 13:19.591
Wow, okay.

13:19.660 --> 13:20.592
Really?

13:20.661 --> 13:22.077
You choose a rotten leg

13:22.180 --> 13:23.526
over chicken waffle bits?

13:23.664 --> 13:25.528
- Yeah, he does this sometimes.
[chuckles]

13:25.666 --> 13:27.358
Last month, he fell in love
with an avocado

13:27.496 --> 13:29.601
and carried it around
till it was mush.

13:29.670 --> 13:30.844
- Is he a rescue?

13:30.982 --> 13:32.190
- Uh, yeah.

13:32.328 --> 13:33.536
Yeah, it took forever
to get him to trust me.

13:33.640 --> 13:36.022
Now he freaks out
if my mom gives me a hug.

13:36.160 --> 13:38.196
- Oh, territorial.
Makes sense.

13:38.334 --> 13:40.681
Um, he has attachment issues.

13:40.785 --> 13:43.961
Maybe if I get
a little closer...

13:44.030 --> 13:45.238
[dog growling]

13:45.341 --> 13:46.929
- Can I?

13:47.033 --> 13:49.518
- Uh, yeah, sure.

13:49.656 --> 13:51.415
[dog growling, barking]

13:51.520 --> 13:52.901
- Oh.
- Hey.

13:54.385 --> 13:55.765
That's good boy.
- Nice.

13:55.869 --> 13:57.388
There.
You see the metal hip joint?

13:57.491 --> 13:59.355
Coroner can use that
to identify the body.

14:01.392 --> 14:03.635
- Is there anything else
we can help with, Officer...

14:03.704 --> 14:05.051
- Celina.

14:05.154 --> 14:06.017
No, thank you.

14:06.121 --> 14:07.881
♪

14:08.019 --> 14:09.710
- Okay. Come on.

14:09.814 --> 14:13.369
♪

14:13.473 --> 14:15.164
- Hey, how'd I do?

14:15.233 --> 14:17.063
- The dumpster diving
was a good tactic.

14:17.166 --> 14:18.547
The DNA was a match.

14:18.650 --> 14:19.651
- Yeah, one man's trash

14:19.720 --> 14:20.894
is a pregnant woman's
case closed.

14:20.998 --> 14:22.413
- Thanks for helping me out.

14:22.516 --> 14:24.242
- Hey, you know,
I could take on another.

14:24.380 --> 14:25.830
I mean, every time
I work one of your cases,

14:25.934 --> 14:27.832
I'm learning just a little bit
more to help me make detective.

14:27.901 --> 14:29.316
- All right.

14:29.420 --> 14:31.491
There's this one witness
to a liquor store burglary,

14:31.594 --> 14:32.733
but I can't get him
to talk to me,

14:32.872 --> 14:34.597
or any cop, for that matter.

14:34.701 --> 14:35.978
- Oh, I bet
I can get him to crack.

14:36.082 --> 14:37.014
- The guy hates the police.

14:37.083 --> 14:38.153
It's impossible.

14:38.256 --> 14:39.326
[quirky music]

14:39.430 --> 14:40.603
But now I have to stop
talking to you,

14:40.741 --> 14:42.467
because Wesley is
staring me down hard.

14:42.571 --> 14:43.848
But I'll send you his name.

14:43.917 --> 14:46.092
♪

14:46.195 --> 14:47.162
Wrong number.

14:47.231 --> 14:48.508
- Oh.

14:48.577 --> 14:50.510
[phone ringing]

14:50.579 --> 14:53.651
[indistinct chatter]

14:54.997 --> 14:55.998
- Hey.

14:56.102 --> 14:57.586
- What's up?

14:58.483 --> 14:59.519
How you doin'?

14:59.588 --> 15:00.761
- Better, now that we've got

15:00.900 --> 15:02.004
some movement on Frank.

15:02.108 --> 15:04.938
I was bored
to early onset rigor mortis.

15:05.076 --> 15:06.595
- Yeah,
crooks have their own schedule.

15:06.698 --> 15:08.355
We call it "dope time."
- Hmm.

15:08.459 --> 15:09.770
- So where are we, case-wise?

15:09.874 --> 15:12.359
- Yeah, he made contact,
asked me to dinner.

15:12.463 --> 15:14.189
- Romantically, like a date?

15:14.292 --> 15:16.225
- Well, ostensibly,
it's about business,

15:16.294 --> 15:18.193
but he did just get
out of prison,

15:18.296 --> 15:20.712
so odds are he's hopeful for
a little somethin'-somethin'.

15:20.816 --> 15:22.542
- Legally, there's two forms
of entrapment.

15:22.645 --> 15:24.061
The first is offering
so much money

15:24.164 --> 15:26.718
that an otherwise reasonable
person commits an illegal act.

15:26.787 --> 15:28.375
The second is sex.

15:28.479 --> 15:30.205
- Yeah, if a UC puts sex
or love on the table

15:30.308 --> 15:31.378
as inducement to crime,

15:31.482 --> 15:33.898
it automatically becomes
entrapment.

15:34.002 --> 15:36.349
- The courts realize that love
makes people do crazy things.

15:36.452 --> 15:38.213
- Right, so I'm--

15:38.316 --> 15:39.386
should we cancel dinner?

15:39.490 --> 15:41.595
- No, but keep it professional.

15:41.664 --> 15:43.459
If he starts saying
that he's doing it for you

15:43.597 --> 15:44.633
or for love, you gotta walk.

15:44.771 --> 15:45.875
- Yeah. Hey.

15:45.979 --> 15:48.395
Should I push a little
about his brother?

15:48.499 --> 15:50.742
- No, because you're still
trying to build a foundation.

15:50.846 --> 15:53.987
Once he trusts you,
he will hang himself.

15:54.091 --> 15:56.610
But we should get
a decent wire for her,

15:56.679 --> 15:58.164
because he could get
a little handsy.

15:58.302 --> 15:59.337
- Mm. All right.

15:59.475 --> 16:01.512
Pull the top of the line
from HIDTA.

16:01.650 --> 16:05.171
We'll reconvene and brief
two hours before your date.

16:05.274 --> 16:06.379
Any questions?

16:07.587 --> 16:08.657
All right.

16:12.661 --> 16:15.664
[tense music]

16:15.767 --> 16:18.943
♪

16:19.012 --> 16:20.565
You okay?

16:20.669 --> 16:22.015
- Five by five.

16:22.153 --> 16:24.086
- You gotta treat this
like any other op

16:24.190 --> 16:26.433
and treat Lucy
like any other UC.

16:26.502 --> 16:28.332
- I know.

16:28.470 --> 16:29.505
- All right.

16:32.577 --> 16:33.854
- Ooh.

16:33.958 --> 16:35.856
Man, it really reeks in here.

16:35.960 --> 16:38.790
- Yeah, Grey is not happy
with Aaron.

16:38.859 --> 16:40.206
[phone chiming, buzzing]

16:40.344 --> 16:42.449
Another match?
- Uh, I don't know.

16:42.553 --> 16:44.520
There is seriously no good man
in Los Angeles--

16:44.624 --> 16:45.935
who are single, of course.

16:46.039 --> 16:47.385
- What about Scott?

16:47.523 --> 16:49.111
- The citizen with the dog?

16:49.215 --> 16:50.457
I don't know.
What about him?

16:50.561 --> 16:51.769
- Well, based on your little
interaction before,

16:51.872 --> 16:53.046
I'd say he was interested.

16:53.150 --> 16:54.047
- [chuckling]
What are you talking about?

16:54.185 --> 16:55.221
No, he wasn't.

16:55.359 --> 16:57.499
- Yes, he was.
Oh, my gosh.

16:57.568 --> 16:58.603
- Why are you smiling?

16:58.707 --> 17:00.053
- Because for someone

17:00.157 --> 17:02.987
who's so connected
to the universe,

17:03.056 --> 17:04.057
you seem a little blind

17:04.194 --> 17:05.576
when it comes
to the romantic signals.

17:05.679 --> 17:07.887
- What signals?
There were no signals.

17:07.992 --> 17:10.546
There were signals?
- [laughs]

17:10.650 --> 17:12.824
Okay, that's not funny.

17:12.928 --> 17:15.241
- You're right.
I'm a little freaked out.

17:15.344 --> 17:18.589
I've never done
anything like this before.

17:18.727 --> 17:21.419
If I get caught,
I'm looking at serious time.

17:21.557 --> 17:22.695
- Prison's not so bad.

17:22.765 --> 17:26.355
You do your time,
meet new business associates.

17:26.424 --> 17:29.876
Most importantly, you learn
what you're really made of.

17:29.945 --> 17:32.189
Helps you see the world
more clearly.

17:32.258 --> 17:33.742
- What did you learn?

17:33.880 --> 17:36.814
- Family can't be trusted.

17:36.917 --> 17:38.954
- Yeah, I hear that.

17:39.058 --> 17:41.094
I mean, the whole reason
I cashed those bogus checks

17:41.198 --> 17:43.821
was 'cause my dad stole
my rent money.

17:43.924 --> 17:45.926
- My brother made a move
against me.

17:46.065 --> 17:47.756
I put him in his place.

17:47.894 --> 17:49.206
- What place is that?

17:49.275 --> 17:51.691
[engine revving]

17:51.760 --> 17:53.520
[dramatic music]

17:53.589 --> 17:55.108
[tires squealing]

17:55.212 --> 17:56.316
Get down!
[gunfire]

17:59.078 --> 18:00.838
[gunfire]

18:00.941 --> 18:02.529
[people screaming]

18:07.120 --> 18:09.295
[tires squealing]

18:09.398 --> 18:11.400
- Put that away--the gun.

18:11.469 --> 18:13.851
- Shots fired,
93107 Wilshire Boulevard,

18:13.954 --> 18:15.715
black Honda Accord headed east.

18:15.784 --> 18:17.855
[suspenseful music]

18:17.958 --> 18:18.856
- Copy that.
- [sighing] Okay.

18:18.959 --> 18:20.409
- Units are on their way.

18:20.478 --> 18:21.410
- In pursuit.

18:21.479 --> 18:22.549
[tires screeching]

18:22.618 --> 18:26.415
[siren wailing]

18:26.484 --> 18:27.968
- We gotta help these people.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.626
- Gotta go!
Cops are on their way!

18:30.730 --> 18:37.323
♪

18:37.461 --> 18:38.358
[horn honking]

18:43.950 --> 18:45.400
- Suspects are out of the car
and on foot.

18:45.503 --> 18:47.333
Driver is a Black male
with a hoodie, headed north.

18:47.471 --> 18:48.679
I'm in foot pursuit
of the shooter.

18:48.782 --> 18:50.163
He's a white male,
brown pants, headed south.

18:50.301 --> 18:52.303
♪

18:58.896 --> 19:02.002
[dog barking]

19:14.912 --> 19:16.327
[gun clicking]

19:17.915 --> 19:19.434
[both grunt]

19:19.537 --> 19:21.263
[siren approaching]

19:21.367 --> 19:23.196
You're under arrest.

19:23.300 --> 19:25.854
♪

19:25.957 --> 19:27.269
Let's go. Get up.

19:27.373 --> 19:28.477
- You okay?

19:28.546 --> 19:30.686
- Yeah. Gun was empty.

19:30.790 --> 19:31.929
I got lucky.

19:32.032 --> 19:33.310
Otherwise...

19:33.379 --> 19:40.351
♪

19:41.214 --> 19:42.215
- What the hell was that?

19:42.319 --> 19:43.389
Were they shooting at you?

19:43.527 --> 19:45.218
- They weren't gunning
for the busboy.

19:45.356 --> 19:48.152
- Hmm, well,
it's been nice knowing you.

19:48.221 --> 19:50.568
Hey!
- You're not backing out here.

19:50.706 --> 19:52.570
Our deal's still on,
you understand me?

19:52.674 --> 19:55.401
- Yeah, ju--just relax, okay?

19:55.504 --> 19:57.161
I'm--I'm scared.

19:57.230 --> 20:00.129
I just--I've never been
shot at before.

20:00.233 --> 20:02.787
- I have.
You'll get used to it.

20:02.891 --> 20:04.686
- Do you know who's after you?

20:04.755 --> 20:07.516
- Two choices.
His guys or my guys.

20:07.585 --> 20:10.174
- "His guys," who?
Your brother?

20:10.243 --> 20:11.658
- Yeah.

20:11.762 --> 20:14.489
Some of his people didn't come
onboard when I took over,

20:14.592 --> 20:16.836
and some of my people
might be feeling

20:16.939 --> 20:18.872
I'm weak enough
to take a shot at.

20:18.941 --> 20:21.150
But they're gonna find out
quick how wrong they are.

20:21.254 --> 20:25.120
- Well, look,
I am in way over my head.

20:25.224 --> 20:27.122
I get that I don't have
a choice on whether or not

20:27.226 --> 20:30.677
I'm helping you, but if you
could just keep the body count

20:30.781 --> 20:32.852
out of my backyard,
that would be great.

20:32.921 --> 20:34.716
- No promises.

20:34.785 --> 20:36.200
Are you okay
to get home by yourself?

20:36.269 --> 20:38.720
- Yeah, no problem.

20:38.789 --> 20:40.342
Thanks for dinner.
- [chuckles]

20:40.446 --> 20:41.688
Yeah.

20:41.757 --> 20:42.655
I'll be in touch.

20:42.758 --> 20:45.865
♪

20:45.934 --> 20:47.901
[car door opens]

20:47.970 --> 20:49.765
[car door closes]
[engine starts]

20:49.869 --> 20:54.011
♪

20:54.114 --> 20:55.184
[phone clicks]

20:55.288 --> 20:56.945
[line ringing]

20:57.048 --> 20:59.188
- Hey, you okay?
- Yeah, you?

20:59.292 --> 21:00.397
- Yeah, I am now.

21:00.466 --> 21:01.812
We got the shooter,
but the driver got away.

21:01.950 --> 21:03.745
Meet me at the laundry room
in your building.

21:03.814 --> 21:06.851
- Yes. See you in 30.

21:06.955 --> 21:08.508
[knock at door]

21:13.306 --> 21:14.307
Hey.
- Hey.

21:14.445 --> 21:15.653
- That was really scary.

21:15.757 --> 21:17.552
- Yeah,
I about had a heart attack.

21:17.655 --> 21:19.070
Does Frank know
who took a run at him?

21:19.174 --> 21:21.556
- Not for sure, but he's
clearly in a tenuous position,

21:21.659 --> 21:23.316
even with his own crew.

21:23.454 --> 21:25.145
- If you need to tap out--
- No.

21:25.284 --> 21:26.837
The fact that
he can't trust anyone

21:26.940 --> 21:28.321
actually strengthens my in.

21:28.459 --> 21:29.564
He needs an ally.

21:29.667 --> 21:31.013
I can be that

21:31.151 --> 21:32.808
and hopefully bring the whole
thing down from within.

21:34.672 --> 21:36.571
- Has he tried anything?

21:36.674 --> 21:39.643
- No, but I can handle it
if he does.

21:39.781 --> 21:41.955
- I know.

21:42.024 --> 21:43.819
- Yeah, knowing
and feeling okay about it

21:43.957 --> 21:45.856
are two different things.

21:45.994 --> 21:47.651
- Look, it's not my first time.

21:48.410 --> 21:49.618
- I know.

21:49.687 --> 21:51.517
It's probably
what makes it worse.

21:52.380 --> 21:53.795
- All right, now's not the time
to talk about this.

21:53.864 --> 21:55.279
I know
you'll bail on the operation

21:55.348 --> 21:56.280
if you don't feel it's safe.

21:56.349 --> 21:57.833
So if you are good, I'm good.

21:57.971 --> 21:59.283
- I'm good.
- Good.

21:59.352 --> 22:00.629
I gotta get back
to the station.

22:00.698 --> 22:02.182
Grey's waiting
for a status update.

22:02.286 --> 22:03.356
- Wait, no, hey.

22:03.494 --> 22:06.359
[soft music]

22:06.497 --> 22:07.774
Lock the door first.

22:07.843 --> 22:10.329
♪

22:15.989 --> 22:17.370
- Told you there were signals.

22:17.508 --> 22:19.199
- What?

22:19.303 --> 22:20.787
Okay, now I'm nervous.
What do I say?

22:20.891 --> 22:22.202
- Well, start with "hello."

22:22.306 --> 22:23.859
I'll be over here.

22:25.620 --> 22:26.862
- [whistling]

22:28.208 --> 22:29.382
both: Hey.

22:29.520 --> 22:31.142
- Hey, hi.

22:31.211 --> 22:33.041
Hey, Buddy.

22:33.179 --> 22:34.629
Look what I have for you.

22:34.732 --> 22:36.493
Here you go.

22:36.596 --> 22:38.633
- Yeah, Buddy was wondering
if we could get that leg back.

22:38.736 --> 22:39.910
He really misses it.

22:40.013 --> 22:41.394
- Ooh, sorry. It's evidence.

22:41.532 --> 22:42.878
So he's just gonna have to find
another one,

22:43.016 --> 22:44.363
which I've discovered,

22:44.432 --> 22:46.226
it actually isn't that hard
to find in Los Angeles.

22:46.330 --> 22:47.883
- Wow, good to know.

22:48.021 --> 22:49.851
Also terrifying.

22:49.920 --> 22:51.680
- Yeah, well,
do you need anything else?

22:51.749 --> 22:53.648
'Cause my boss is waiting.
- Uh, no.

22:53.751 --> 22:55.650
Well, yes. Sorry.

22:55.753 --> 22:56.996
I've been on dating apps
so long,

22:57.099 --> 22:59.654
I've forgotten how to ask
someone out in real life.

22:59.757 --> 23:02.070
- Dating apps are the worst.

23:03.761 --> 23:06.833
Wait.
Are you about to ask me out?

23:06.902 --> 23:08.041
- I am.

23:08.110 --> 23:10.319
Uh, do you wanna get
dinner tonight,

23:10.423 --> 23:11.942
or tomorrow,

23:12.080 --> 23:13.081
or really,
whenever you're free?

23:13.184 --> 23:14.358
- I'd like that.

23:14.427 --> 23:17.326
I know a great place
with a dog-friendly patio.

23:17.430 --> 23:19.328
- Oh, we love
a dog-friendly patio.

23:19.432 --> 23:20.537
- Great. It's a date.

23:20.606 --> 23:22.090
- [chuckles]
- That rhymed.

23:22.228 --> 23:23.436
- Yes, it did.

23:23.540 --> 23:26.094
- Uh, don't be late,
or I'll be irate.

23:26.197 --> 23:27.889
- Ooh.

23:27.958 --> 23:29.166
- Yeah, went a little bit far.

23:29.269 --> 23:31.030
- Just a little bit.
- Celina!

23:31.099 --> 23:32.756
- I gotta go, but uh, here.

23:32.894 --> 23:33.860
Here's my card.

23:33.929 --> 23:35.034
Call me--or text me,

23:35.137 --> 23:36.656
or whatever people do
these days.

23:36.760 --> 23:38.658
- Okay.

23:41.627 --> 23:44.215
- Hi.
- Hey, uh, good news.

23:44.319 --> 23:47.011
The M.E. got the serial number
off the prosthetic hip joint

23:47.115 --> 23:48.116
from that last leg,

23:48.254 --> 23:50.394
so he is no longer "NoHo Doe."

23:50.463 --> 23:51.913
His name is Trip Linden,

23:51.982 --> 23:54.122
and he was reported missing
a month ago.

23:54.260 --> 23:55.641
- Well, who reported him?

23:55.779 --> 23:57.781
[laughter]
- Dude, this is ridiculous.

23:57.919 --> 23:59.058
- Hi.

23:59.127 --> 24:00.646
Uh, Detective Harper.

24:00.784 --> 24:02.579
Thank you for coming in.

24:02.648 --> 24:05.374
Can you tell me your names
so I know who's who?

24:05.478 --> 24:07.031
- Um, Mark.

24:07.135 --> 24:09.033
- Hank.

24:09.137 --> 24:10.759
- Okay, great, and uh,

24:10.828 --> 24:13.831
I understand you're both
friends with Trip Linden?

24:13.935 --> 24:15.902
- Yeah. Yeah, did you find him?

24:15.971 --> 24:18.491
- I'm afraid we did.

24:18.629 --> 24:19.906
Parts of him.

24:20.010 --> 24:21.218
- Wait, wait.
What does that mean?

24:21.321 --> 24:23.323
- We found his torso

24:23.427 --> 24:24.877
and one of his legs.

24:27.396 --> 24:28.674
- They look scared.

24:28.812 --> 24:30.330
- Dismemberment is scary.

24:30.469 --> 24:32.022
That doesn't mean
they're guilty.

24:32.125 --> 24:34.507
- [scoffs]
That's messed up, man.

24:34.611 --> 24:37.579
- I'm sorry to be the bearer
of such upsetting news.

24:37.683 --> 24:39.512
Were the three of you close?

24:39.650 --> 24:41.514
- Yeah, yeah.
We hung out all the time.

24:41.652 --> 24:43.343
You know,
he had the sickest collection.

24:43.482 --> 24:44.862
Have you ever shot an RPG?

24:45.000 --> 24:46.692
Just...
- [chuckling] Come on, man.

24:46.830 --> 24:48.866
- Trip owned an RPG?

24:49.004 --> 24:52.629
- No, no.
I mean, not if it's illegal.

24:52.698 --> 24:54.596
Look, he definitely
never broke the law.

24:54.700 --> 24:56.702
- Okay, and I understand
the two of you

24:56.805 --> 24:58.048
reported him missing?

24:58.151 --> 25:00.050
- Yeah, 'cause the last time
we saw him,

25:00.153 --> 25:01.879
he was heading to Vegas and--

25:01.983 --> 25:02.880
to meet up with some chick,

25:02.984 --> 25:04.330
and he just never came back.

25:04.399 --> 25:05.883
- I mean, if they had something
to do with his death,

25:05.987 --> 25:07.367
they wouldn't have
reported him missing.

25:07.506 --> 25:09.197
- You'd be surprised
how many people think

25:09.300 --> 25:11.164
that'll throw us off the scent.

25:11.233 --> 25:12.959
- Uh, can you describe
this woman?

25:13.028 --> 25:14.478
- Oh, no, sorry.

25:14.547 --> 25:15.997
We never met her.

25:16.066 --> 25:19.241
- Maybe she did something
to him, you know?

25:19.379 --> 25:23.660
Like...like she was the lure
to some sicko.

25:23.729 --> 25:24.902
- Theorizing.

25:25.040 --> 25:26.076
That's never a good sign.

25:26.179 --> 25:27.733
- Maybe he's just trying
to be helpful.

25:27.836 --> 25:29.562
- No, they're trying
to offer up another suspect.

25:29.666 --> 25:31.219
- All right,
we will look into her.

25:31.322 --> 25:33.048
Did Trip have any enemies?

25:33.186 --> 25:34.912
- No, no. Trip was the best.

25:35.016 --> 25:37.087
Not that bright, but--
- Hey, yo.

25:37.190 --> 25:38.398
Don't speak ill of the dead,
man.

25:38.537 --> 25:39.572
Come on.

25:39.676 --> 25:40.918
- Sorry.

25:41.056 --> 25:42.575
- He was not that bright?

25:42.713 --> 25:45.164
- No, he just--he didn't make
the best of choices,

25:45.267 --> 25:47.407
but he was a great guy, really.

25:47.511 --> 25:49.030
Either of us had a problem,

25:49.099 --> 25:51.584
and he was always there for us.

25:51.722 --> 25:53.862
- See if you can corroborate
any part of that story.

25:53.931 --> 25:56.002
- Will do, and I'll check
their social media too.

25:56.106 --> 25:58.315
I've become a black belt in
Googling the lies out of men.

25:58.418 --> 25:59.316
[elevator bell dings]

25:59.419 --> 26:00.317
- I'm here, y'all,

26:00.420 --> 26:01.836
in the belly of the beast.

26:01.939 --> 26:03.769
Tune in to the next video
to see what happened.

26:03.907 --> 26:07.013
Oh, and uh, remember
to like and subscribe.

26:07.117 --> 26:08.601
- Mr. Perry,
thanks for coming in

26:08.705 --> 26:09.947
to talk about the robbery.

26:10.051 --> 26:11.535
- You're welcome,
but like I told

26:11.639 --> 26:13.710
the pregnant detective,
I don't wanna get involved.

26:13.779 --> 26:15.435
I only came in to shoot
some ClipTalk videos.

26:15.574 --> 26:16.540
- Hey, look, I get it, okay?

26:16.609 --> 26:17.783
You don't wanna talk
to the cops.

26:17.921 --> 26:19.336
Most people don't.

26:19.439 --> 26:21.372
But we know
you saw the robbery.

26:21.476 --> 26:22.857
You were right outside
the store when it happened.

26:22.960 --> 26:24.030
So is there anything
you remember

26:24.134 --> 26:26.377
of the driver
or the car or an--

26:26.446 --> 26:28.034
- Not a chance.
- Look.

26:28.138 --> 26:30.519
I got 4 million followers
on ClipTalk.

26:30.623 --> 26:32.038
- What? No, you don't.

26:32.142 --> 26:33.453
- Yes, I do.
[phone clicks]

26:35.559 --> 26:38.355
I could tag you,
get your name out there.

26:39.632 --> 26:41.289
- You have to do
better than that.

26:41.427 --> 26:42.359
Dance challenge.

26:42.462 --> 26:43.912
[upbeat music]

26:43.981 --> 26:45.051
- ♪ Watch out, 'cause

26:45.155 --> 26:46.466
♪ I'm coming your way, yeah

26:46.570 --> 26:48.399
♪ Nonstop, I can do this
all day, yeah ♪

26:48.503 --> 26:50.125
♪ Go work
what your mama done gave ya ♪

26:50.263 --> 26:51.540
♪ Mama done gave ya

26:51.644 --> 26:52.921
♪ Mama, mama done gave ya

26:52.990 --> 26:54.336
♪ Whole world all yours

26:54.440 --> 26:55.924
♪ For the taking,
bring it home ♪

26:55.993 --> 26:57.477
- What in the hell?

26:57.581 --> 26:58.547
- Sorry, sir.

26:58.651 --> 27:00.549
Just, um, cracking
another case.

27:01.827 --> 27:03.552
- ♪ Mama done gave ya
- What in the hell?

27:03.656 --> 27:04.761
- This is awesome.

27:04.830 --> 27:07.177
Uh, guy who robbed
the liquor store.

27:07.315 --> 27:10.490
License plate started with 3JR,
silver Accord.

27:10.629 --> 27:12.320
- 3JR. Yes!

27:12.423 --> 27:13.424
Okay.

27:13.493 --> 27:16.496
[dog barking]

27:20.500 --> 27:21.985
[phone chimes]

27:22.088 --> 27:24.988
[engine revving]

27:25.091 --> 27:28.336
[tires squealing]

27:28.439 --> 27:29.751
- Get in!
- Frank.

27:29.855 --> 27:32.236
- Now!
- O--okay.

27:32.340 --> 27:35.930
[suspenseful music]

27:36.033 --> 27:36.965
What's wrong?

27:37.034 --> 27:39.036
- I know who shot at us.

27:39.174 --> 27:40.244
I gotta take him down.

27:40.348 --> 27:41.798
I need a lookout.

27:41.867 --> 27:43.662
♪

27:46.699 --> 27:49.633
[tires squealing]

27:49.702 --> 27:52.636
[tense music]

27:52.705 --> 27:55.190
♪

27:55.328 --> 27:57.020
[gun clicking]

27:57.123 --> 27:58.469
- Where are we?

27:58.573 --> 28:00.264
- This is where
all the magic happens.

28:00.368 --> 28:02.163
3D printers are inside.

28:02.232 --> 28:04.717
- Okay, wait, so you think
it was one of your guys

28:04.821 --> 28:07.202
who took a run at you?
- Yeah, Grant.

28:07.306 --> 28:08.238
You stay out here.

28:08.341 --> 28:09.929
Call me if you see anything.

28:10.033 --> 28:17.040
♪

28:19.732 --> 28:20.802
[phone ringing]

28:20.906 --> 28:22.045
- Hey.

28:22.183 --> 28:23.356
Why are you here?

28:23.425 --> 28:25.358
- Okay, so Frank's driver
was the shooter,

28:25.427 --> 28:26.912
and now I'm acting
as his lookout

28:27.050 --> 28:28.016
while he goes inside
to kill him.

28:28.085 --> 28:29.846
What exactly is my play here?

28:29.915 --> 28:31.330
- First priority is
to stop a murder.

28:31.399 --> 28:32.676
So be a good lookout.

28:32.745 --> 28:35.023
Every cop in LA is about
to land on this location.

28:35.092 --> 28:37.543
- Okay.
- All right, bye.

28:37.612 --> 28:39.890
8-500, I need additional units
at my location.

28:40.028 --> 28:40.960
Code-3.

28:41.064 --> 28:44.343
♪

28:44.412 --> 28:47.346
[hip-hop music playing]

28:47.415 --> 28:50.142
- [rapping indistinctly]

28:50.245 --> 28:54.491
♪

28:54.594 --> 28:55.768
[glass clinking]

28:55.906 --> 28:57.943
[laughter]

28:58.046 --> 29:01.084
[suspenseful music]

29:01.187 --> 29:04.052
[laughter]

29:04.121 --> 29:05.882
- Hey, we gotta go.
The cops are coming.

29:05.951 --> 29:07.297
- How?
- I don't know.

29:07.400 --> 29:08.850
But we don't have much time.

29:08.954 --> 29:10.714
Frank, you are an ex-con
with a gun.

29:10.783 --> 29:12.026
I don't know anything
about law,

29:12.129 --> 29:13.096
but I'm pretty sure
that sends you back.

29:13.234 --> 29:14.166
Let's go.

29:14.269 --> 29:15.270
Come on.

29:15.408 --> 29:16.962
♪

29:17.100 --> 29:19.447
[sirens wailing]

29:19.585 --> 29:22.622
[tires squealing]

29:29.353 --> 29:32.356
[sirens wailing]

29:47.820 --> 29:49.649
- The car matches
Morgan's description

29:49.788 --> 29:50.823
of the robbery vehicle.

29:50.961 --> 29:51.997
- Anything inside?

29:52.135 --> 29:53.239
- Not that I can see,

29:53.343 --> 29:55.310
but I haven't checked
the trunk yet.

30:04.768 --> 30:05.734
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

30:05.838 --> 30:08.082
- [coughing]

30:08.185 --> 30:10.222
- The air fresheners
are just making it worse.

30:10.325 --> 30:11.361
- Yeah.

30:11.499 --> 30:14.502
7-Adam-7,
I have a possible 187.

30:14.640 --> 30:15.606
[flies buzzing]

30:15.675 --> 30:18.333
Alley off of 1700 block
on Tustin.

30:18.471 --> 30:19.852
Send detectives and TID.

30:19.956 --> 30:22.855
[dramatic music]

30:22.959 --> 30:24.684
♪

30:24.823 --> 30:26.686
[muffled dance music playing]

30:26.825 --> 30:29.344
- [singing in Spanish]

30:29.482 --> 30:30.690
- Police!

30:30.794 --> 30:32.416
♪

30:32.520 --> 30:33.762
Anyone in there?

30:33.866 --> 30:37.042
♪

30:37.145 --> 30:38.629
Show me your hands.

30:38.698 --> 30:41.184
♪

30:41.287 --> 30:42.288
[music stops]

30:43.427 --> 30:44.704
We got another body.

30:46.706 --> 30:48.191
[phone clicks]

30:48.329 --> 30:49.882
[phone chimes]

30:50.020 --> 30:51.815
Looks like this guy died
of a heart attack.

30:51.884 --> 30:53.334
- How can you tell?

30:53.403 --> 30:55.715
- His search says
"signs of a heart attack."

30:55.819 --> 31:00.410
Okay, so after
a successful burglary spree,

31:00.548 --> 31:03.516
heart attack and trunk guy
get into a disagreement, right?

31:03.585 --> 31:05.760
Which leads
to trunk guy's death,

31:05.898 --> 31:08.728
and then heart attack puts
trunk guy in the trunk,

31:08.832 --> 31:10.282
tries to cover the smell
before he can decide

31:10.385 --> 31:11.593
what to do with him,

31:11.697 --> 31:14.079
makes it all the way back here
to the auto shop,

31:14.217 --> 31:16.598
and then the effort
was a bit too much and...

31:16.702 --> 31:19.429
[snaps fingers]
Pop goes his heart.

31:19.567 --> 31:21.396
- That's some good detecting.

31:21.534 --> 31:22.742
- I know, right?

31:22.881 --> 31:24.468
- Vegas PD struck out.

31:24.572 --> 31:25.607
They have no record of Trip

31:25.745 --> 31:27.368
coming to town
with a mystery woman.

31:27.437 --> 31:30.440
- But IT was able to get
into Trip's cloud account.

31:30.543 --> 31:33.374
Turns out he enjoyed making
videos with Mark and Hank.

31:33.443 --> 31:34.823
- What kind of videos?

31:34.927 --> 31:37.205
- Not that kind of videos.
Worse.

31:37.274 --> 31:40.277
- In one of the clips,
they shot a cow with an RPG.

31:40.381 --> 31:41.796
- What is wrong with people?

31:41.934 --> 31:45.420
- After combing through
several soul-crushing hours

31:45.558 --> 31:47.767
of footage, we found that.

31:47.906 --> 31:49.217
[gunfire]
[laughter]

31:49.286 --> 31:51.116
- All right,
what am I looking at?

31:51.219 --> 31:54.291
- The idiots got their hands
on a .50 caliber machine gun.

31:54.429 --> 31:56.293
[gunfire]
[laughter]

31:56.431 --> 31:57.881
- They're just blowing up
watermelons.

31:57.985 --> 32:01.954
- Right, until Trip goes out
onto the range and...

32:02.058 --> 32:03.438
[gunshot]
[laughter stops]

32:03.542 --> 32:04.646
- There goes his head.

32:04.784 --> 32:07.201
- Trip!
He's dead! What do we do?

32:07.304 --> 32:10.135
- Well, that is definitely
enough to get a warrant.

32:10.238 --> 32:11.791
- Right, so what do you say

32:11.895 --> 32:14.380
we let SWAT go
and take care of arresting

32:14.484 --> 32:15.968
the heavily armed survivalists?

32:16.106 --> 32:17.038
- Where's the fun in that?

32:17.142 --> 32:19.316
- [laughs]
- Let's go.

32:19.454 --> 32:20.628
- I mean, she's--
she's kidding, right?

32:20.731 --> 32:22.181
- I'm afraid not. [sighs]

32:26.047 --> 32:27.807
- [panting]

32:27.946 --> 32:29.395
That was crazy.

32:29.499 --> 32:31.915
How the hell am I supposed
to go to the office after that?

32:31.984 --> 32:33.399
[gun clicks]

32:33.503 --> 32:35.367
- You got ten seconds
to convince me

32:35.470 --> 32:36.575
you're not a cop.

32:36.644 --> 32:39.474
♪

32:42.477 --> 32:45.170
[tense music]

32:45.308 --> 32:47.620
- I'm not a cop. I...

32:47.689 --> 32:50.658
- Then how the hell did you
know they were coming?

32:50.796 --> 32:52.832
A police scanner app.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.317
I can show you.

32:54.420 --> 32:55.697
- A what?

32:55.835 --> 32:57.837
- A police scanner app.
Can--can I just...

33:02.187 --> 33:03.429
Look.

33:03.533 --> 33:05.362
I have never been
a lookout before, okay?

33:05.500 --> 33:06.950
So when you ran inside,

33:07.019 --> 33:08.193
I thought this might be useful.

33:08.331 --> 33:09.849
I downloaded it,
and the first thing I heard

33:09.988 --> 33:11.679
was the warehouse address.

33:11.817 --> 33:14.371
I--I almost peed my pants!

33:14.475 --> 33:16.201
- You could've just run,

33:16.339 --> 33:18.858
left me inside
to get killed or arrested.

33:20.377 --> 33:22.552
Why didn't you?

33:22.655 --> 33:23.691
- Honestly,
it didn't occur to me,

33:23.829 --> 33:25.210
although at this moment,

33:25.313 --> 33:28.178
I--I really, really wish I had.

33:29.283 --> 33:31.526
- [sighs]

33:32.838 --> 33:36.393
When you're about to be
released from prison,

33:36.497 --> 33:38.706
those last few weeks,
you're just dreaming,

33:38.809 --> 33:42.330
you know,
about the outside world.

33:42.399 --> 33:44.988
All the things you're gonna do,

33:45.057 --> 33:47.128
all the meals you're gonna eat,

33:47.232 --> 33:49.406
all the money
you're gonna make,

33:49.544 --> 33:51.995
the women you're gonna--

33:52.064 --> 33:53.479
well, you get it.

33:53.548 --> 33:54.894
- Yeah.

33:56.137 --> 33:59.416
- But you know,
then you get out,

33:59.520 --> 34:01.142
the world's different.

34:03.662 --> 34:05.388
It's moved on without you.

34:07.424 --> 34:10.255
And the place
you thought you held in it,

34:10.358 --> 34:12.326
it doesn't exist anymore.

34:12.429 --> 34:15.915
You realized you've, you know,
lost a step or two.

34:17.020 --> 34:19.609
- Eight years is a long time.

34:19.712 --> 34:22.094
- Yeah, and I wasn't exactly

34:22.232 --> 34:23.853
a millennial when I went in.

34:23.958 --> 34:27.099
- There's gotta be other things
you were dreaming about inside

34:27.237 --> 34:30.275
besides money, food, and women.

34:30.413 --> 34:32.346
- Yeah, my kid.

34:32.449 --> 34:34.313
But she took off
when I got out.

34:34.417 --> 34:35.935
- Why?

34:36.074 --> 34:37.937
- Look,
I was never a good dad.

34:38.076 --> 34:41.112
Always wrapped up
in being the tough guy,

34:41.251 --> 34:43.114
causing mayhem, getting paid,

34:43.253 --> 34:44.634
making money.

34:44.737 --> 34:47.947
She--well, gave her
no time at all.

34:48.085 --> 34:49.397
She deserved better.

34:49.466 --> 34:51.503
- You could reach out now,

34:51.606 --> 34:53.125
try to fix things.

34:53.263 --> 34:54.851
Where is she?

34:54.954 --> 34:57.233
- Ohio.

34:57.302 --> 34:58.717
She tried going off the grid

34:58.820 --> 35:01.720
so I couldn't find her,
you know?

35:01.789 --> 35:03.480
But I found her pretty easy.

35:03.584 --> 35:05.241
- You could visit.

35:05.310 --> 35:07.070
You know,
try to make things right.

35:07.139 --> 35:09.555
- Nah.

35:09.659 --> 35:12.455
She'll never forgive me.

35:12.593 --> 35:14.284
- Maybe not.

35:15.665 --> 35:17.598
Even if she doesn't, though,

35:17.667 --> 35:19.634
it'll matter that you tried.

35:19.738 --> 35:23.431
[soft music]

35:23.500 --> 35:25.433
I just met you.
I don't know you.

35:25.502 --> 35:28.333
But it really seems like
you don't wanna be

35:28.436 --> 35:30.887
living your life
like this anymore.

35:30.990 --> 35:32.130
- [chuckles]

35:35.098 --> 35:37.238
I should go.
- Okay.

35:38.343 --> 35:41.346
- Hey, uh, thanks again.

35:41.484 --> 35:44.107
And I'm sorry about,
you know...

35:44.176 --> 35:48.353
- Threatening my life
on multiple occasions?

35:48.491 --> 35:50.251
[laughs] Yeah.

35:50.355 --> 35:51.494
Bygones.

35:58.846 --> 36:00.365
Frank.

36:00.503 --> 36:01.780
I'll see you later.

36:01.849 --> 36:03.368
- Hmm.

36:03.506 --> 36:05.784
Not if I see you first.

36:10.547 --> 36:13.205
[phone ringing]

36:13.343 --> 36:14.379
- Where are you?

36:14.482 --> 36:15.621
- I'm outside
the cover apartment.

36:15.725 --> 36:17.485
Frank just dropped me off.

36:17.554 --> 36:19.901
- We grabbed Grant
and the other two,

36:20.039 --> 36:22.387
got enough weaponry
to hold them until we try

36:22.525 --> 36:24.043
to get a ballistics match
for the restaurant shooting

36:24.182 --> 36:25.493
and Ed's murder.

36:25.562 --> 36:27.875
- Yeah, fingers crossed.

36:28.013 --> 36:30.291
I think this op is done.

36:30.395 --> 36:31.982
- You sure?

36:32.051 --> 36:32.983
- Yeah.

36:33.052 --> 36:35.400
I mean, he's got no crew,

36:35.538 --> 36:37.125
no product.

36:37.229 --> 36:38.575
It's over.

36:38.679 --> 36:40.922
- That's too bad.
- Why?

36:41.026 --> 36:43.373
- I was looking forward
to another laundry room hookup.

36:45.099 --> 36:46.928
[siren wailing]
- We couldn't find his fingers.

36:47.066 --> 36:48.896
He tried to evade arrest
using a grenade launcher,

36:49.034 --> 36:51.139
and--and failed.
- It hurts! Ahh!

36:51.243 --> 36:52.969
[groaning]

36:53.072 --> 36:55.178
- Hey, uh,
I put a BOLO out for Mark.

36:55.247 --> 36:56.869
Hopefully we can get him
before he finds out

36:56.938 --> 36:58.423
there's an arrest warrant
for him.

36:58.561 --> 36:59.941
[elevator bell dings]
- Right.

37:00.045 --> 37:02.530
- I don't think
that'll be a problem.

37:02.599 --> 37:03.704
- Hey, excuse me.

37:03.773 --> 37:04.877
I heard my friend
was brought in

37:04.946 --> 37:06.914
in some kind
of explosives accident.

37:07.052 --> 37:09.882
- Mark, hey.
Hank is in treatment.

37:09.951 --> 37:11.850
Uh, we just need
to talk to you.

37:11.919 --> 37:13.196
- Stay back!

37:13.265 --> 37:14.542
We didn't mean to hurt Trip.

37:14.611 --> 37:15.923
[tense music]

37:16.061 --> 37:17.476
It was an accident.

37:17.580 --> 37:18.512
♪

37:18.581 --> 37:20.410
[grunting]

37:22.274 --> 37:24.276
- Nice work, Mama.

37:24.380 --> 37:25.553
OB appointment?

37:25.622 --> 37:27.624
- Yeah. What?

37:27.728 --> 37:30.109
I couldn't just stand here
and do nothing.

37:33.216 --> 37:34.113
- Detective.

37:34.252 --> 37:35.183
Grey said
you were looking for me.

37:35.287 --> 37:36.461
- Uh, yes.

37:36.599 --> 37:38.463
Remember that arm
the M.E. flagged at the morgue?

37:38.566 --> 37:40.327
- Yeah, the one with
the, uh, unique cut?

37:40.465 --> 37:42.467
- Yeah, well, it might not
have been related to NoHo Doe,

37:42.605 --> 37:45.021
but it is related
to a case in Arizona.

37:45.124 --> 37:47.057
A coroner there found an arm

37:47.161 --> 37:48.921
that was severed
with that same mystery tool,

37:48.990 --> 37:52.028
and both were done while
the victim was still alive.

37:52.131 --> 37:53.719
- That's horrible,

37:53.823 --> 37:55.721
and it means we're looking
at a possible serial killer.

37:55.825 --> 37:56.791
Should we be calling the feds?

37:56.895 --> 37:58.137
- Yeah, I already did.

37:58.241 --> 38:00.485
- John Nolan.
- As I live and breathe,

38:00.623 --> 38:01.969
Simone Clark,
what a pleasure to see you.

38:02.107 --> 38:03.384
- Pleasure to be seen.

38:03.488 --> 38:05.006
What up, girl?
- Hey, Simone.

38:05.144 --> 38:07.215
- Does this mean Garza's unit
is taking this case?

38:07.319 --> 38:08.424
- Oh, yeah.

38:08.493 --> 38:10.080
It's the reason
I joined the FBI,

38:10.184 --> 38:12.117
so that I could swoop in
and steal the thunder

38:12.186 --> 38:14.326
right out from under
local law enforcement.

38:14.430 --> 38:15.396
- Technically,
you're not required

38:15.500 --> 38:16.604
to rub our noses in it.

38:16.673 --> 38:18.675
- But where's the fun in that?

38:18.813 --> 38:21.057
Why don't you bring me
up to speed on everything,

38:21.160 --> 38:23.093
and then I can steal
your theories

38:23.162 --> 38:24.888
and pawn them off as my own?

38:24.992 --> 38:26.338
[ultrasound whooshing]

38:26.476 --> 38:28.167
- Baby looks great.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.273
Angela,
you're on the home stretch.

38:30.377 --> 38:33.103
- Thank God, because I'm
strictly at the loafer stage.

38:33.172 --> 38:34.829
I can't tie my shoelaces
anymore.

38:36.106 --> 38:37.176
- Hey.

38:37.315 --> 38:38.661
Sorry to interrupt.

38:39.420 --> 38:41.042
- What are you doing here?

38:41.180 --> 38:43.251
- I, uh, just wanted to deliver
the news in person.

38:43.355 --> 38:45.530
- I texted you
to meet me in the lobby.

38:45.633 --> 38:46.669
- Seriously?

38:47.808 --> 38:49.637
- Baby, you know
how I feel about open cases.

38:49.706 --> 38:52.433
I promise I'll be ready
to nest after this.

38:52.537 --> 38:53.676
- Please tell me
you closed the case.

38:53.779 --> 38:54.642
- Oh, better.

38:54.711 --> 38:56.334
I closed seven cases.

38:57.196 --> 38:58.543
- Well done, Officer Thorsen.

38:58.681 --> 39:01.408
I'll make sure
Caradine knows you stepped up.

39:01.511 --> 39:03.962
- Yeah, and also, thank you
so much for the opportunity.

39:04.031 --> 39:05.481
Yeah.

39:06.309 --> 39:10.037
You know, Aaron is a great
girl's name too, so...

39:11.625 --> 39:13.489
- We--we were waiting
to be surprised.

39:13.558 --> 39:16.492
[Hayden Calnin's
"Warm With You"]

39:16.561 --> 39:18.390
♪

39:18.494 --> 39:19.736
- [sighs]

39:19.874 --> 39:22.118
I need a big meal, a hot bath,

39:22.221 --> 39:24.396
and some quality sexy time,

39:24.500 --> 39:27.606
and then I'm gonna sleep
for 24 hours.

39:28.918 --> 39:30.851
What, what is that? What?

39:30.920 --> 39:33.405
- I just--
Isabel used to always crash

39:33.509 --> 39:34.751
after a long-term assignment.

39:34.889 --> 39:36.995
It would take her months
to come back to life.

39:38.341 --> 39:40.412
- Well, this was only a week,

39:40.516 --> 39:43.933
so I think one night's sleep
will do me.

39:44.071 --> 39:45.486
You know what?
I do have to come clean

39:45.590 --> 39:46.660
about something, though.

39:46.729 --> 39:47.730
Um...

39:49.248 --> 39:50.940
I know I made you promise

39:51.043 --> 39:53.529
to not watch "Top Chef"
without me,

39:53.598 --> 39:54.668
but I couldn't wait!

39:54.737 --> 39:55.979
I'm sorry!

39:56.083 --> 39:57.671
- ♪ We could build a house

39:57.774 --> 39:59.017
- Bad girlfriend.
- No.

39:59.086 --> 40:00.812
- No.
- No, I'm sorry!

40:00.915 --> 40:01.813
- Horrible.

40:01.916 --> 40:04.332
♪

40:04.436 --> 40:05.506
- So...

40:05.610 --> 40:07.128
♪

40:07.266 --> 40:08.785
Why didn't you tell me
you almost died

40:08.923 --> 40:11.339
chasing down the shooter
at the restaurant?

40:11.443 --> 40:12.789
- Because I didn't.

40:12.927 --> 40:15.033
- [scoffs]
- Who told you?

40:15.102 --> 40:16.793
- It doesn't matter.

40:16.897 --> 40:18.933
We'll set aside the fact that
you left it out of the report

40:19.037 --> 40:20.866
so I wouldn't find out.

40:20.935 --> 40:22.523
- I did not.

40:22.627 --> 40:23.628
- What?

40:23.731 --> 40:25.112
- Okay.

40:25.250 --> 40:26.907
The gun was empty, right?

40:26.976 --> 40:29.150
So this is
much ado about nothing.

40:29.288 --> 40:31.359
Besides, I know for a fact that
you don't tell me everything

40:31.463 --> 40:32.740
that happens to you
when you're undercover.

40:32.809 --> 40:35.294
- N--no, no.

40:35.433 --> 40:38.056
You know for a fact
that Isabel didn't.

40:39.057 --> 40:40.714
If this is gonna work
between us,

40:40.817 --> 40:43.233
I need to know that
you can see the difference.

40:43.302 --> 40:45.132
- Of course I can.

40:45.235 --> 40:47.168
Okay? But...

40:47.306 --> 40:48.929
listen, I need you
to take it seriously

40:48.998 --> 40:50.896
if I ever sound the alarm
about something.

40:51.656 --> 40:52.898
Otherwise, the pain
of what I went through

40:53.002 --> 40:54.106
will have been for nothing,

40:54.175 --> 40:57.731
and I can't lose you
the way I lost her.

40:58.559 --> 41:00.492
- You won't.

41:00.596 --> 41:02.839
I'll walk away
before it ever gets close

41:02.977 --> 41:05.497
to anything like that, okay?

41:05.635 --> 41:07.154
I promise.

41:07.257 --> 41:11.296
♪

41:11.365 --> 41:15.852
- ♪ We could build a house
away from here ♪

41:15.956 --> 41:17.509
- Good luck on your date.

41:17.647 --> 41:19.684
- Thank you.
I'm really excited.

41:19.822 --> 41:21.202
Maybe I should just throw
some tarot cards,

41:21.340 --> 41:23.032
you know, just to make sure
Scott and I have a future.

41:23.170 --> 41:25.172
- Or maybe you should
just live your life

41:25.310 --> 41:26.760
and see where it takes you.

41:26.863 --> 41:27.933
- That's so much scarier.

41:28.037 --> 41:29.763
- Yeah, sure,
but it's that discovery

41:29.866 --> 41:31.696
that makes it
so much more special.

41:31.799 --> 41:33.352
Look, take Bailey and me.

41:33.456 --> 41:35.700
We have not landed
on a wedding date yet,

41:35.838 --> 41:38.185
but I know when that day comes,

41:38.323 --> 41:39.876
it's gonna be amazing.

41:40.014 --> 41:41.119
- You're getting married
in September.

41:41.188 --> 41:43.397
- [chuckles] Nice try.

41:43.535 --> 41:45.192
We're not talking about
anything before next spring.

41:45.295 --> 41:46.883
- That's nice, but trust me.

41:46.987 --> 41:48.713
It's gonna happen in September.

41:48.851 --> 41:50.300
- Because you threw down
some tarot cards?

41:50.369 --> 41:51.716
- No.

41:51.819 --> 41:52.889
- Don't stay out too late,

41:52.993 --> 41:54.546
have fun,
and text me when you get home.

41:54.684 --> 41:56.065
- Yes, sir.

41:56.168 --> 42:00.034
♪ Yeah, I just wanted warmth
with you ♪

42:00.172 --> 42:04.867
♪

42:04.970 --> 42:06.593
- Hey.

42:06.696 --> 42:08.526
What do you think about
getting married in September?

42:11.390 --> 42:14.324
[dramatic music]

42:14.393 --> 42:21.400
♪

42:44.354 --> 42:45.424
- Damn it.
